## Phase 3: Physics - Constellation Spring Constraint

### 3.1 New Force Function

**File to modify**: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Universe\utils\cosmicPhysics.js`

Add a new exported function after `computeStarPullOffsetsFromEmbeddings`:

```javascript
/**
 * Compute additional pull offsets for constellation-linked star pairs.
 * These act as stiff springs pulling linked stars toward each other.
 * 
 * @param {Array} constellations - Array of { star_id_a, star_id_b } objects
 * @param {Map} computedStarPositions - Map<postId, {x, y}> of current star positions  
 * @param {Object} options - { springStrength, idealDistance, maxOffset }
 * @returns {Map<postId, {dx, dy}>} Additional pull offsets per star
 */
export const computeConstellationPullOffsets = (
    constellations,
    computedStarPositions,
    {
        springStrength = 0.03,
        idealDistance = 200,
        maxOffset = 120,
    } = {}
) => {
    const offsets = new Map();
    if (!Array.isArray(constellations) || constellations.length === 0) return offsets;
    if (!(computedStarPositions instanceof Map)) return offsets;

    for (const link of constellations) {
        const posA = computedStarPositions.get(link.star_id_a);
        const posB = computedStarPositions.get(link.star_id_b);
        if (!posA || !posB) continue;

        const dx = posB.x - posA.x;
        const dy = posB.y - posA.y;
        const dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        const displacement = dist - idealDistance;

        // Spring force: pull toward each other if farther than idealDistance,
        // push apart if closer (acts like a rest-length spring)
        const force = displacement * springStrength;
        const fx = (dx / dist) * force;
        const fy = (dy / dist) * force;

        // Accumulate offset for star A (pulled toward B)
        if (!offsets.has(link.star_id_a)) offsets.set(link.star_id_a, { dx: 0, dy: 0 });
        const offsetA = offsets.get(link.star_id_a);
        offsetA.dx += fx;
        offsetA.dy += fy;

        // Accumulate offset for star B (pulled toward A)
        if (!offsets.has(link.star_id_b)) offsets.set(link.star_id_b, { dx: 0, dy: 0 });
        const offsetB = offsets.get(link.star_id_b);
        offsetB.dx -= fx;
        offsetB.dy -= fy;
    }

    // Clamp magnitudes
    for (const [postId, offset] of offsets.entries()) {
        offsets.set(postId, clampOffsetMagnitude(offset, maxOffset));
    }

    return offsets;
};
```

### 3.2 Integrate into Star Position Pipeline

**File to modify**: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Universe\Universe.jsx`

The `getComputedStarPosition` callback (line 178) currently computes:
```
finalX = baseX + galDx + pull.dx
finalY = baseY + galDy + pull.dy
```

We need to add constellation pull offsets. The approach is to compute constellation offsets as a `useMemo` that depends on `computedStarPositions` from `InteractiveLayer` and the constellation data, then merge them into the position calculation.

However, since constellation offsets depend on already-computed positions (which include galaxy displacement + existing pull offsets), this creates a circular dependency. The correct approach is:

**Strategy**: Constellation offsets are computed from the base star positions (before constellation offsets are applied), then added as an additional layer. This is the same pattern used by `starPullOffsets` -- they compute offsets from base positions, not from final positions.

In `Universe.jsx`, add:

```javascript
// State for constellation data
const [constellations, setConstellations] = useState([]);

// Fetch constellations when posts change (debounced, similar to wormhole fetch)
useEffect(() => {
    // ... fetch constellations for visible post IDs via getViewportConstellations
}, [postArray]);

// Constellation pull offsets (computed from base positions + galaxy displacement, 
// similar to how starPullOffsets are computed in useCosmicGravity)
const constellationPullOffsets = useMemo(() => {
    if (constellations.length === 0) return new Map();
    // Build intermediate positions map (base + galaxy + existing pull, before constellation)
    const basePositions = new Map();
    for (const post of postArray) {
        const pos = getComputedStarPosition(post);
        if (pos) basePositions.set(post.id, pos);
    }
    return computeConstellationPullOffsets(constellations, basePositions);
}, [constellations, postArray, getComputedStarPosition]);
```

Then update `getComputedStarPosition` to also include `constellationPullOffsets`:

```javascript
const getComputedStarPosition = useCallback((post) => {
    // ... existing logic ...
    const cPull = constellationPullOffsets.get(post.id);
    return {
        x: baseX + galDx + (pull?.dx ?? 0) + (cPull?.dx ?? 0),
        y: baseY + galDy + (pull?.dy ?? 0) + (cPull?.dy ?? 0),
    };
}, [galaxyPositions, starPullOffsets, constellationPullOffsets]);
```

**Important consideration**: To avoid circular dependency (constellation offsets computed from positions that include constellation offsets), we should compute constellation offsets from the "pre-constellation" positions. The cleanest approach is to have a `preConstellationPosition` function that excludes constellation offsets, compute constellation offsets from those, then add them in the final `getComputedStarPosition`.

---

## Phase 4: Visual Rendering - ConstellationLayer

### 4.1 New Layer Component

**File to create**: `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Universe\layers\ConstellationLayer.jsx`

This follows the exact pattern of `WormholeLayer.jsx` -- a `React.memo` component using `Layer` + `Shape` with `sceneFunc` and `requestAnimationFrame` for continuous animation:

```javascript
import React, { useRef, useEffect, useCallback, useMemo } from 'react';
import { Layer, Shape } from 'react-konva';
import { STAR_COLORS, hexToRgba } from '../utils/starUtils';

const TWO_PI = Math.PI * 2;

const parseHex = (hex) => ({
    r: parseInt(hex.slice(1, 3), 16),
    g: parseInt(hex.slice(3, 5), 16),
    b: parseInt(hex.slice(5, 7), 16),
});

const ConstellationLayer = React.memo(({ layerProps, constellations, computedStarPositions, zoom }) => {
    const animRef = useRef({ time: 0 });
    const shapeRef = useRef(null);
    const rafRef = useRef(null);

    // Pre-compute visual data with colors
    const linkData = useMemo(() => {
        if (!Array.isArray(constellations)) return [];
        return constellations
            .filter(c => c.status === 'accepted')
            .map((c, i) => {
                const color = STAR_COLORS[i % STAR_COLORS.length];
                const rgb = parseHex(color);
                return { ...c, color, rgb };
            });
    }, [constellations]);

    // Pending links shown with different style
    const pendingData = useMemo(() => {
        if (!Array.isArray(constellations)) return [];
        return constellations.filter(c => c.status === 'pending');
    }, [constellations]);

    const animate = useCallback(() => {
        animRef.current.time = performance.now();
        if (shapeRef.current) {
            shapeRef.current.getLayer()?.batchDraw();
        }
        rafRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
    }, []);

    useEffect(() => {
        if (linkData.length === 0 && pendingData.length === 0) return;
        rafRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
        return () => {
            if (rafRef.current) cancelAnimationFrame(rafRef.current);
        };
    }, [animate, linkData.length, pendingData.length]);

    if (linkData.length === 0 && pendingData.length === 0) return null;

    const drawConstellationLink = (ctx, ax, ay, bx, by, rgb, time) => {
        // Solid glowing line (distinct from wormhole dashed lines)
        const mx = (ax + bx) / 2;
        const my = (ay + by) / 2;

        // Outer glow
        ctx.save();
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${rgb.r},${rgb.g},${rgb.b},0.08)`;
        ctx.lineWidth = 6;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(ax, ay);
        ctx.lineTo(bx, by);
        ctx.stroke();

        // Main solid line
        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(${rgb.r},${rgb.g},${rgb.b},0.35)`;
        ctx.lineWidth = 2;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(ax, ay);
        ctx.lineTo(bx, by);
        ctx.stroke();

        // Animated energy pulse (bright dot traveling along the line)
        const pulseT = ((time * 0.0003) % 1);
        const px = ax + (bx - ax) * pulseT;
        const py = ay + (by - ay) * pulseT;
        const pulseAlpha = 0.6 + 0.3 * Math.sin(time * 0.003);

        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.arc(px, py, 3, 0, TWO_PI);
        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(${rgb.r},${rgb.g},${rgb.b},${pulseAlpha})`;
        ctx.fill();

        ctx.restore();

        // Label at midpoint (if label exists)
        // This would be handled separately with Konva Text nodes for proper hit detection
    };

    const drawPendingLink = (ctx, ax, ay, bx, by) => {
        // Dim dashed line for pending constellations
        ctx.save();
        ctx.setLineDash([6, 8]);
        ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(255,255,255,0.12)';
        ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        ctx.beginPath();
        ctx.moveTo(ax, ay);
        ctx.lineTo(bx, by);
        ctx.stroke();
        ctx.setLineDash([]);
        ctx.restore();
    };

    return (
        <Layer {...layerProps} listening={false}>
            <Shape
                ref={shapeRef}
                sceneFunc={(ctx) => {
                    const time = animRef.current.time;
                    const positions = computedStarPositions;

                    // Draw accepted constellation links
                    for (const link of linkData) {
                        const posA = positions.get(link.star_id_a);
                        const posB = positions.get(link.star_id_b);
                        if (!posA || !posB) continue;
                        drawConstellationLink(ctx, posA.x, posA.y, posB.x, posB.y, link.rgb, time);
                    }

                    // Draw pending constellation links
                    for (const link of pendingData) {
                        const posA = positions.get(link.star_id_a);
                        const posB = positions.get(link.star_id_b);
                        if (!posA || !posB) continue;
                        drawPendingLink(ctx, posA.x, posA.y, posB.x, posB.y);
                    }
                }}
                perfectDrawEnabled={false}
                listening={false}
            />
        </Layer>
    );
});

ConstellationLayer.displayName = 'ConstellationLayer';
export default ConstellationLayer;
```

